race.comment: SER JOH (5) carried the same weight to be beaten under a length by the smart Chief Witness in a similar race here two runs back. Struggled last start when he went back to 1200m. Back in his right race today and from a good draw he gets every chance. RED DEFCON (10) enjoyed the drop in grade and step up in trip when second-up last start, closing well to get up for third over 1350m at Doomben. Has placed three from four at this stage of the campaign, and her record at or around seven furlongs is outstanding. Right in contention. BATTLEFIELD (2) was six weeks between runs when a barnstorming third over this distance at the Sunny Coast last weekend. Fitter and races well here so a big run is expected. CASTILLIAN (6) had good form last time in. Readied with a trial and draws the inside so looking for a strong return.
